thread.title_full: Embraer 2Q net profit down 10.6% | Manufacturers content from ATWOnline

author: Aaron Karp
title: Embraer 2Q net profit down 10.6% | Manufacturers
text:
Embraer reported second-quarter net income of $131.1 million, down 10.6% from a net profit of $146.7 million in the 2014 June quarter, on a 14.2% year-over-year drop in revenue to $1.51 billion.
Embraer delivered 27 commercial aircraft in the second quarter, down slightly from 29 commercial aircraft delivered in the prior-year period. Second-quarter 2015 commercial deliveries comprised 22 E-175s, three E-190s and two E-195s.
The Brazilian manufacturer’s second-quarter operating profit decreased 25.6% from $385.2 million in the 2014 June quarter to $286.7 million this year.
Commercial aircraft now represent 58.3% of Embraer’s total revenue, up from 55.2% in the 2014 second quarter. The company noted that the E-Jet E2 program has now secured 267 firm orders.
